{
  "stem": "10572.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my uncle, with his two sons, were also on the train.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In the-- while we were on the train-- and still didn't know yet where we were going, and one of the worst punishments and greatest fear was this uncertainty.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, nobody told you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You didn't get an itinerary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the sun was rising over the city.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was well known to us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we somehow felt maybe we never see the city again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a friend of my father-- and I don't know how he got it in-- had a book, that he carried in-- with him.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And my father tore the cover page out of the and converted it into a postcard and wrote a postcard to my mother-- and lied that we were fine, and that we had confidence, and we wanted them to be brave and have faith.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now was the trick-- how did we get this postcard posted?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father asked one of the SS guards, appealing to his better instincts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, would you do me a favor and put a stamp on this and mail it to my wife?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The postcard arrived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So the train moved.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And little by little, we started to realize by the towns we got through, that we were on our way to Buchenwald near Weimar.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we arrived in Weimar.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one of the men in our [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] compartment in the train was our doctor, Dr.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Cohen, Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Leopold Cohen, who had lost his left leg during the First World War as a surgeon on the front and was known in Hildersheim always with a black cane in order to-- and he was on our train.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
